{"parse":{"title":"Roger Gaillard (historian)","pageid":7833707,"revid":818711361,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Roger_Gaillard.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Roger_Gaillard.JPG/220px-Roger_Gaillard.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"180\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Roger_Gaillard.JPG/330px-Roger_Gaillard.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Roger_Gaillard.JPG/440px-Roger_Gaillard.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"654\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Roger_Gaillard.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Roger Gaillard at his residence in <a href=\"/wiki/Kenscoff\" title=\"Kenscoff\">Kenscoff</a> of 1973.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Roger Gaillard</b> (10 April 1923 &#8211; 2000) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Haiti\" title=\"Haiti\">Haitian</a> historian and novelist. Born in <a href=\"/wiki/Port-au-Prince\" title=\"Port-au-Prince\">Port-au-Prince</a>, Gaillard earned a philosophy degree at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Paris\" title=\"University of Paris\">University of Paris</a> in France. He is best known for his multiple-volume chronicle of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_occupation_of_Haiti_(1915-1934)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States occupation of Haiti (1915-1934)\">United States' occupation of Haiti</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_works\">Selected works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roger_Gaillard_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>L'Univers Romanesque de <a href=\"/wiki/Jacques_Roumain\" title=\"Jacques Roumain\">Jacques Roumain</a></i> (1965)</li>\n<li><i>La Destin\u00e9e de <a href=\"/wiki/Carl_Brouard\" title=\"Carl Brouard\">Carl Brouard</a></i> (1966)</li>\n<li><i>Les Cent Jours de <a href=\"/wiki/Rosalvo_Bobo\" title=\"Rosalvo Bobo\">Rosalvo Bobo</a></i> (1973)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Charlemagne_P%C3%A9ralte\" title=\"Charlemagne P\u00e9ralte\">Charlemagne P\u00e9ralte</a> le Caco</i> (1982)</li>\n<li><i>La Gu\u00e9rilla de Batraville</i> (1983)</li>\n<li><i>La D\u00e9route de l'Intelligence</i> (1992)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roger_Gaillard_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Schutt-Ain\u00e9, Patricia (1994). <i>Haiti: A Basic Reference Book</i>. Miami, Florida: Librairie Au Service de la Culture. p.&#160;103. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-9638599-0-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-9638599-0-0\">0-9638599-0-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Haiti%3A+A+Basic+Reference+Book&amp;rft.place=Miami%2C+Florida&amp;rft.pages=103&amp;rft.pub=Librairie+Au+Service+de+la+Culture&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=0-9638599-0-0&amp;rft.aulast=Schutt-Ain%C3%A9&amp;rft.aufirst=Patricia&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARoger+Gaillard+%28historian%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wi